<?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" href="http://www.jewishstudies.umd.edu/faculty/Lapin/MishnahProject/TestMishnahStyleSheet.css" title="Mishnah Style Sheet" alternate="no"?>
<TEI xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader>
        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Title</title>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt>
                <p>Publication Information</p>
            </publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc>
                <p>Citations of the Mishnah from commentaries. Begun with explicit references to
                    readings in <ref ana="#MelSh">Melekhet Shelomoh</ref>. </p>
                <p>In the reading groups included below, <gi>ref</gi> refers to the authority/ies
                    citing the reading; <gi>wit</gi>to the authority/ies to whom the reading is
                    attributed. <!-- Should be listed in ref.xml? -->
                    <!-- Needs considerable fleshing out -->
                    <listWit>
                        <witness xml:id="Rosh">Rosh</witness>
                        <witness xml:id="Rif">Rif</witness>
                        <witness xml:id="MelSh">Melekhet Shelomoh</witness>
                        <witness xml:id="YAshk">Yehohanan Ashkenazi</witness>
                    </listWit></p>
            </sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
        <encodingDesc>
            <p>Uses the structure of critical apparatus module combined with xpointer to allow the
                file to point to the relevant <gi>w</gi> elements in ref.xml. Where the lemma is a
                single word, the <att>corresp</att> attribute on <gi>lem</gi> uses the
                    <att>xml:id</att> on <gi>w</gi> in ref.xml to construct the URI. When it refers
                to two or more words, the URI is constructed out of an xpointer scheme as in
                    <val>ref.xml#range(string-range(xpath1(id('ref.4.2.2.3.19')), 0, 0),
                    xpath1(id('ref.4.2.2.3.24'))</val>.</p>
        </encodingDesc>
    </teiHeader>
    <text>
        <body>
            <ab xml:id="commcit.4.2.2.8">
                <app>
                    <rdgGrp>
                        <!-- Since this is is to a single word, I use a simple URI -->
                        <lem type="cit" corresp="ref.xml#ref.4.2.2.8.17">
                            <ref type="Com"/>
                        </lem>
                        <rdg>כתחילה<wit corresp="#MelS"/><ref ana="#MelS"/></rdg>
                    </rdgGrp>
                    <rdgGrp>
                        <lem type="cit"><!-- Since this is is to a single word, I use a simple URI -->
                            <ref type="Com"/>
                        </lem>
                        <rdg>יִלְמַד<wit corresp="#YAshk"/><ref ana="#MelSh"/></rdg>
                        <rdg>יִלַמֵּד<wit corresp="#MelSh"/><ref ana="#MelSh"/></rdg>
                        <!-- How deal with this. Cites two readings, the second (above) according to
                        R. Yehosef.-->
                    </rdgGrp>
                    <rdgGrp>
                        <lem type="cit"
                            corresp="ref.xml#range(string-range(xpath1(id('ref.4.2.2.2.8.53'))),
                            xpath1(id('ref.4.2.2.2.8.62'))"/>
                        <rdg>מצא שק או קפה אם אין דרכו ליטול<wit corresp="#Rif #Rosh #YAshk"/><ref
                                ana="#MelSh"/></rdg>
                    </rdgGrp>
                </app>
            </ab>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
